19 member of the Council to:
20 (a) Make up the time he or she is absent from work to carry
21 out his or her duties as a member of the Council; or
22 (b) Take annual leave or compensatory time for the absence.
23 7. As used in this section, “historically underserved
24 community” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 704.78343.
25 Sec. 4. 1. The Council shall:
26 (a) Establish and administer a program to award a designation
27 to:
28 (1) Schools in this State which provide to pupils outdoor
29 education programs that meet the standards developed pursuant to
30 section 5 of this act; and
31 (2) A teacher in this State as Outdoor Educator of the Year.
32 (b) Provide opportunities for educators to receive training
33 concerning outdoor education by developing such training or
34 identifying and making available to schools information
35 concerning opportunities for such training.
36 (c) Provide technical assistance to support schools and school
37 districts interested in developing initiatives for outdoor education.
38 In providing such assistance, the Council shall prioritize schools
39 with the least access to nature.
40 (d) Identify sources of federal money and grants to support
41 outdoor education in this State.
42 2. The Division:
