3 Sec. 5. 1. In administering the program established
4 pursuant to section 4 of this act, the Council shall:
5 (a) Develop voluntary standards for outdoor education
6 programs provided to pupils by schools, including, without
7 limitation, standards:
8 (1) Which provide for an interdisciplinary approach for a
9 curriculum of outdoor education; and
10 (2) Concerning the development and use of living
11 schoolyards which are climate-resilient; and
12 (b) Provide a nonmonetary award to a teacher recognized
13 pursuant to section 4 of this act as Outdoor Educator of the Year.
14 2. For the purposes of this section, “living schoolyard”
15 means an outdoor environment at a school that strengthens local
16 ecological systems and serves as a resource for hands-on
17 education, including, without limitation, trees, gardens, outdoor
18 meeting areas and other areas designed for such purposes.
19 Sec. 6. The Council may adopt such regulations as are
20 necessary to carry out the provisions of sections 4 and 5 of this act.
